{"id": "EUVD-2025-4782", "enisaUuid": "8ab5a2c7-b03c-365e-b0b8-5275ec32ab82", "description": "When reading the language .mo file in grub_mofile_open(), grub2 fails to verify an integer overflow when allocating its internal buffer. A crafted .mo file may lead the buffer size calculation to overflow, leading to out-of-bound reads and writes. This flaw allows an attacker to leak sensitive data or overwrite critical data, possibly circumventing secure boot protections.", "datePublished": "2025-02-18T19:25:45", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-11T08:13:09", "baseScore": 6.7, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-45776", "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-45776", "https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=2339182", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2025:6990", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2025:16154"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-45776", "GHSA-8852-57vj-5pjq"], "assigner": "redhat", "epss": 0.07, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "4a4d75eb-fca8-3c3f-af1a-c1a17436bdc1", "product": {"name": "Red Hat Enterprise Linux 10"}, "product_version": "patch: 1:2.12-15.el10_0"}, {"id": "9280c20e-f693-3d38-a0f8-dde0e567042d", "product": {"name": "Red Hat Enterprise Linux 9"}, "product_version": "patch: 1:2.06-104.el9_6"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "5c36ea5a-620c-3c05-b439-a05f58cb96f9", "vendor": {"name": "Red Hat"}}], "isExploited": false}